    summary: "The Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program (NSNP) held a Physician Stream draw on April 18, 2026, inviting 35 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 591.",
    body: "The Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program (NSNP) held a Physician Stream draw on April 18, 2026, inviting 35 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 591.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the NSNP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in Nova Scotia, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Physician Stream, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The NSNP reviews provincial applications within 111 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from Nova Scotia adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of Nova Scotia prioritising occupations in construction, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, NSNP has issued approximately 5,840 invitations across all streams.\n\n\"The Federal Court has been increasingly receptive to procedural fairness arguments — this is consistent with that trend,\" noted IRPP fellow Élise Bouchard.\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within two weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
