    id: "n0193",
    slug: "northwest-territories-ntnp-invites-580-candidates-in-skilled-worker-draw",
    title: "Northwest Territories NTNP invites 580 candidates in Skilled Worker draw",
    summary: "The Northwest Territories Provincial Nominee Program (NTNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on April 13, 2026, inviting 580 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 584.",
    body: "The Northwest Territories Provincial Nominee Program (NTNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on April 13, 2026, inviting 580 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 584.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the NTNP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in Northwest Territories, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Skilled Worker, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The NTNP reviews provincial applications within 109 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from Northwest Territories adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of Northwest Territories prioritising occupations in agriculture, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, NTNP has issued approximately 4,053 invitations across all streams.\n\nImmigration lawyer Catherine Sauvé warned that \"candidates outside the favoured category should reconsider their timing — and their backup plan.\"\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within three weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
