    slug: "northwest-territories-ntnp-invites-22-candidates-in-skilled-worker-draw-2",
    title: "Northwest Territories NTNP invites 22 candidates in Skilled Worker draw",
    summary: "The Northwest Territories Provincial Nominee Program (NTNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on March 30, 2026, inviting 22 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 701.",
    body: "The Northwest Territories Provincial Nominee Program (NTNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on March 30, 2026, inviting 22 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 701.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the NTNP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in Northwest Territories, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Skilled Worker, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The NTNP reviews provincial applications within 91 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from Northwest Territories adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of Northwest Territories prioritising occupations in construction, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, NTNP has issued approximately 4,788 invitations across all streams.\n\nSettlement-sector analyst Nadia Petrov said the change \"shifts pressure onto provinces to expand their PNP capacity, particularly in healthcare-heavy regions.\"\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within two weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
