    slug: "ircc-issues-7-500-itas-in-express-entry-draw-369-transport-occupations-crs-478",
    title: "IRCC issues 7,500 ITAs in Express Entry draw #369 (Transport occupations, CRS 478)",
    summary: "Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada conducted Express Entry draw #369 on February 12, 2026, issuing 7,500 invitations to apply under the Transport occupations stream with a minimum CRS score of 478.",
    body: "Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada conducted Express Entry draw #369 on February 12, 2026, issuing 7,500 invitations to apply under the Transport occupations stream with a minimum CRS score of 478.\n\nThis was the 12th draw of the year and the 3rd under the Transport occupations category since IRCC formally re-categorised its Express Entry approach. The previous draw under the same category had a cut-off of 474, putting this round on a tightening trajectory of 4 CRS points.\n\nCandidates with a Notification of Interest profile in the Express Entry pool who met the Transport occupations criteria and scored at or above 478 on the Comprehensive Ranking System were issued an Invitation to Apply. Eligibility for this category is governed by section 10.3 of IRCC's category-based selection instructions, which require either an eligible NOC 2021 occupation, a French-language CLB 7+ result, or both, depending on the category in question.\n\nSuccessful candidates now have 60 days to submit a complete electronic application for permanent residence (e-APR). Required documentation includes police certificates from every country of residence for six months or more since age 18, an upfront medical examination from a panel physician, proof of settlement funds (where applicable), and reference letters that match the lead-statement and main-duties of the declared NOC. Applications submitted late or incomplete are rejected without refund of the processing fee.\n\nToronto-based RCIC Meena Ramachandran called it \"a long-overdue alignment between IRCC operational practice and the Levels Plan.\"\n\nThe next Express Entry draw is expected within seven to fourteen days. Chrome Visa Solutions will publish a follow-up brief if the upcoming round is targeted at a different category. Candidates currently in the pool should re-confirm their NOC code under NOC 2021, refresh language scores nearing their two-year expiry, and ensure their proof-of-funds figure reflects the latest LICO threshold.",
