    id: "n0225",
    slug: "saskatchewan-sinp-invites-580-candidates-in-tech-talent-pathway-draw",
    title: "Saskatchewan SINP invites 580 candidates in Tech Talent Pathway draw",
    summary: "The Saskatchewan Provincial Nominee Program (SINP) held a Tech Talent Pathway draw on September 11, 2025, inviting 580 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 484.",
    body: "The Saskatchewan Provincial Nominee Program (SINP) held a Tech Talent Pathway draw on September 11, 2025, inviting 580 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 484.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the SINP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in Saskatchewan, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Tech Talent Pathway, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The SINP reviews provincial applications within 68 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from Saskatchewan adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of Saskatchewan prioritising occupations in early childhood education, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, SINP has issued approximately 2,901 invitations across all streams.\n\nToronto-based RCIC Meena Ramachandran called it \"a long-overdue alignment between IRCC operational practice and the Levels Plan.\"\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within three weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
