    slug: "nova-scotia-nsnp-invites-35-candidates-in-entrepreneur-draw",
    title: "Nova Scotia NSNP invites 35 candidates in Entrepreneur draw",
    summary: "The Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program (NSNP) held a Entrepreneur draw on December 03, 2024, inviting 35 candidates with a minimum ranking score of 82.",
    body: "The Nova Scotia Provincial Nominee Program (NSNP) held a Entrepreneur draw on December 03, 2024, inviting 35 candidates with a minimum ranking score of 82.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the NSNP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in Nova Scotia, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Entrepreneur, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The NSNP reviews provincial applications within 78 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from Nova Scotia adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of Nova Scotia prioritising occupations in manufacturing, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, NSNP has issued approximately 6,317 invitations across all streams.\n\nCILA spokesperson Daniel Park noted that \"the change does not alter eligibility, but it materially changes the strategy for profile creation.\"\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within four weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
