    summary: "The New Brunswick Provincial Nominee Program (NBPNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on November 05, 2024, inviting 145 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 710.",
    body: "The New Brunswick Provincial Nominee Program (NBPNP) held a Skilled Worker draw on November 05, 2024, inviting 145 candidates with a minimum CRS score of 710.\n\nCandidates were drawn from the NBPNP Expression of Interest system, which ranks profiles using a points matrix that weighs work experience, education, language ability, employment in New Brunswick, and family ties to the province. Streams aligned with Express Entry, like the Skilled Worker, also require an active EE profile to be eligible for a provincial nomination.\n\nSuccessful applicants now have 45 days to submit a full provincial nomination application along with supporting evidence: language test results (IELTS, CELPIP, or TEF/TCF), educational credential assessments, employment records that map to a TEER 0–5 occupation, and proof of settlement funds. The NBPNP reviews provincial applications within 106 days under current service standards. Receiving a provincial nomination from New Brunswick adds 600 CRS points to a candidate's federal Express Entry profile, effectively guaranteeing an Invitation to Apply at the next federal draw.\n\nThis draw fits a wider pattern of New Brunswick prioritising occupations in manufacturing, in line with the province's labour market gap analysis published earlier this year. Year-to-date, NBPNP has issued approximately 4,578 invitations across all streams.\n\n\"This is the operational follow-through on commitments IRCC made in last year's departmental plan,\" observed analyst Karim Hossain.\n\nCandidates not invited in this round but with active EOI profiles will remain in the pool for the next draw, typically held within four weeks. Chrome Visa Solutions recommends that candidates whose ranking score sits within 30 points of the cut-off review their language test schedule and verify whether a higher CLB band would lift them into invitation range.",
